decks.notes: This deck focuses on utilizing aggressive creatures and spells to quickly overwhelm the opponent and deal damage efficiently. Cards like Gut, True Soul Zealot and Scion of Halaster provide strong creatures to attack with, while removal spells like Lightning Bolt and Terminate help control the board. Additionally, the deck includes cards like Bloodsoaked Champion and Pyrokinesis to maintain tempo and pressure the opponent. The goal is to establish early board presence, disrupt the opponent's strategy with hand disruption spells like Thoughtseize and Hymn to Tourach, and close out the game with powerful finishers like Kroxa, Titan of Death's Hunger. The deck aims to win through aggressive and efficient combat while disrupting the opponent's game plan.

The main concept of this deck is to play aggressively with a focus on controlling the board and disrupting your opponent's plans. Satya, Aetherflux Genius is the commander that enables this strategy, providing card advantage and flexibility in your plays. With a mix of efficient creatures like Cathar Commando and strong removal spells like Swords to Plowshares, the deck aims to pressure the opponent and protect its own threats. By utilizing cards like Hullbreacher and Force of Will, you can disrupt your opponent's plans while building up your own board presence. The mana base is designed to support the color-intensive spells in the deck, ensuring you can consistently cast your key cards and apply pressure throughout the game.
